fields.description:
I encounter this error on opening a branch-based worktree (git worktree add [...]) :
{{git status' failed with code 128:'fatal: Not a git repository}}

Note that does not happen on the latest SourceTree For Windows.

after pushing a small changeset (a few kb) to our mercurial server, i get a much increased traffic utilization. The system-monitor shows some "python" processes are causing a lot of traffic. After that single push about 3GB! the push contains one changeset and 3 merges (3 different branches).

the processlist says this (the push has run through some minutes ago):
{{
ottos-mbp:~ otto$ ps aux|grep hg
otto            23519   1,5  0,3  2485592  25116   ??  S     4:16pm   0:18.83 /usr/bin/python /usr/local/bin/hg incoming --template='rev={node}^J' -q default
otto            23815   1,5  0,3  2483364  22980   ??  S     4:18pm   0:06.48 /usr/bin/python /usr/local/bin/hg incoming --template='rev={node}^J' -q default
otto            23518   1,5  0,3  2485592  26264   ??  S     4:16pm   0:18.79 /usr/bin/python /usr/local/bin/hg incoming --template='rev={node}^J' -q default
otto            24044   0,0  0,0  2434840    636 s000  R+    4:20pm   0:00.00 grep hg
}}

This still leaves an empty line in the global git config:


{code}
[mergetool "sourcetree"]
    cmd = 
{code}
